            <p align="justify">&nbsp;</p>
            <p align="justify">1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ex Gratia Disability allce is awarded to Army pers who are invalided out with 100% disability 
            and provided Constant Attendant Allowance permanently for diseases/conditions of total blindness, paraplegia, quadriplegia, irreversible comatose
            condition due to irreversible Brain damage as a result of trauma, infection, stroke or any cause leading to permanent vegetative state or equivalent,
            persons loosing two limbs i.e. Amputation of both legs (Above Knee) and both Arms (Above Elbow) and are dependant on others for their day to day activities 
            and survival. This will be in addition to the normal disability benefit. The corpus fund of ₹ 25 Lakh for Offrs and ₹ 12.5 Lakh for JCOs/OR are invested by 
            Army Group Insurance Fund in a fixed deposit of a Nationalised Bank and the interest earnings is given to the beneficiary during his life period only. 
            This will cease on his demise and the corpus fund will revert to Army Group Insurance Fund.</p>
